HEADWORD: Nisan
<hw>Ni"san</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Heb.
<ets>n⟦imac⟧s⟦amac⟧n</ets>.]</ety> <def>The first month of the Jewish
ecclesiastical year, formerly answering nearly to the month of April,
now to March, of the Christian calendar. See <er>Abib</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

